solution.text:
Height of passage,h\(=_{j}_\,cm\)
Width of passage,w\(=_{k}_\,cm\)
Rate of air flow,r\(=_{l}_\,\frac{m}{hr}=_{{Fraction(l*5,3)}}_ \, \frac{cm}{min}\)
Volume of air collected in \(1\) min\(=h \times w \times r\)
\(=_{{Fraction(j*k*l*5,3)}}_\,\frac{cm^3}{min}\)
Therefore, amount of compressed air collected in \(_{m}_\) minutes \(=\) Volume of air collected in \(1\) minute \(\times\) Time
\(=_{{Fraction(j*k*l*5,3)}}_ \times _{m}_\)
\(=_{{trunc(((j*k*l*5*m)/Decimal(3)),3)}}_\,cm^3\)

content.text: Compressed air is flowing through a passage of \(_{j}_\, cm\) deep and \(_{k}_\, cm\) wide at the rate of \(_{l}_\,\frac{m}{hr}\) into a large reservoir. How much air is collected in the reservoir after \(_{m}_\)minutes?
